A pleasant, quiet, peaceful and warm place. The Swedish institute is beautiful to visit both for the works put forward by the artists, but also for its magnificent garden hidden in the marsh. Once relaxed, don't miss the cafÃ© Fika, a nice place with waitresses just adorable, they are also trilingual (Swedish, French and English) so practical, nice and with great advice. You will have at your disposal to entertain your friends/children... pencils to draw or to draw the cutlery of the coffee to go (great idea). The coffees and drinks are super good, the food and desserts are delicious, especially at reasonable prices !! The concept of this cafÃ© is just too cool and I can't wait to come back to drink my coffees after college. I would like to thank the waitresses Rose and especially Venice for the service provided from June 12 until the closing of July.

She felt so bad, she insisted that he check hers. Racial profiling isn't fun especially when an African does it to another black person.
